                                                                  6037 1451
 The resolved resonance parameters are adopted from the           6037 1451
 ATLAS [Mu06].  The upper energy region of the resolved resonance 6037 1451
 parameters is truncated at 7.6 keV in order to properly take     6037 1451
 into account the p-wave contribution in the unresolved           6037 1451
 resonance region. The parameters of the bound level are then     6037 1451
 modified  to reproduce a  bound coherent scattering  amplitude   6037 1451
 of 8.7-+0.2 fm and a thermal capture cross section of 1.49 b.    6037 1451
 As a starting point, the average resolved  resonance parameters  6037 1451
 are adopted from the ATLAS [Mu06]. Where                         6037 1451
 average values are not recommended in [Mu06], the relevant       6037 1451
 quntities are derived from the systematics as described in the   6037 1451
 figures [Mu06]. Adjustments are then carried out until  the      6037 1451
 calculations  agreed with Wisshak et al. data [Wi98]. Since      6037 1451
 the inelastic theshold opens at a high energy, 0.45 MeV, an      6037 1451
 energy dependent radiative width is invoked on the basis of the  6037 1451
 the Mughabghab-Dunford model [Mu00]                              6037 1451
